Others: Malaysia and Kuwait have advanced to the regional final of T20 World Cup 2026 qualification after placing top of the table in a group that included Hong Kong, Singapore, Maldives, Myanmar and Mongolia.
The pair will move to a hybrid Asia/East Asia-Pacific regional final of nine teams, with three World Cup spots up for grabs.
Hong Kong started strong with four wins on the trot to start the tournament, only dropping one close game to eventual winners Malaysia.
Kuwait showed their batting power smashing Mongolia by 160 runs and then Maldives by 142 runs.
Syed Aziz was the star for Malaysia, making 216 runs at a handy strike rate of 174 and taking 4/9 against Hong Kong.
Yasin Patel’s 15 wickets at an economy of 4.85 and Shiraz Khan’s eight wickets at an economy of 4.75 complemented Kuwait’s batting prowess.
